HOUSE BILL 1587
C7 6lr3639
By: Delegate Patterson
Introduced and read first time: February 15, 2026
Assigned to: Rules and Executive Nominations
Re–referred to: Ways and Means, February 26, 2026
Committee Report: Favorable with amendments
House action: Adopted
Read second time: March 23, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Gaming – Operation of Electronic Instant Bingo Machines – Operation and
3 Maximum Number of Machines and Report by State Lottery and Gaming
4 Control Agency
5 FOR the purpose of altering the definition of “slot machine” to repeal a limitation on
6 increase the number of bingo cards certain handheld devices may allow a user to
7 play at the same time; increasing the number of electronic instant bingo machines
8 that certain entities may operate; providing that an electronic instant bingo machine
9 is not required to print a paper ticket for each instant bingo game played except
10 under certain circumstances; requiring the State Lottery and Gaming Control
11 Agency, on or before a certain date, to report to the Governor and the General
12 Assembly regarding certain matters concerning certain electronic instant bingo and
13 satellite simulcast facilities; and generally relating to electronic instant bingo
14 machines gaming.
15 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
16 Article – Criminal Law
17 Section 12–301, 12–301.1(e), and 12–308
18 Annotated Code of Maryland
19 (2021 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
20 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
21 Chapter 603 of the Acts of the General Assembly of 2012
22 Section 3
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
